1
00:00:03,229 --> 00:00:09,710
Devotees understand, you get the ... 
And by observing the pastimes 
of Mahāprabhu ...

2
00:00:09,754 --> 00:00:14,257
Mahāprabhu's pastimes put 
all the emphasis upon Prabhu-priya,

3
00:00:14,257 --> 00:00:15,835
the one of who is most 
dear to Kṛṣṇa.

4
00:00:16,025 --> 00:00:19,003
[Krishna As Krishna Das]

5
00:00:19,143 --> 00:00:23,244
yadi gaura nā hoito, tabe ki hoito,
kemone dharitām de

6
00:00:23,244 --> 00:00:27,355
rādhār mahimā, prema-rasa-sīmā,
jagate jānāto ke

7
00:00:27,355 --> 00:00:31,988
In fact here Vāsudev Ghoṣ is saying, 
“This is why Mahāprabhu came down.”

8
00:00:33,362 --> 00:00:37,126
Someone will say, “Well, I thought 
He came to give Kṛṣṇa-prema.”

9
00:00:37,480 --> 00:00:39,900
“Well, where does Kṛṣṇa-prema 
come from?”

10
00:00:42,257 --> 00:00:43,731
They’ll say, “Oh, from Kṛṣṇa.”

11
00:00:43,731 --> 00:00:48,773
Yeah, but who ... Kṛṣṇa is not 
the receptacle of Kṛṣṇa-prema.

12
00:00:50,097 --> 00:00:53,557
He is the object of Kṛṣṇa-prem.

13
00:00:53,557 --> 00:00:57,017
He is not the one 
possessing the prema for Kṛṣṇa

14
00:00:57,017 --> 00:01:00,479
until He embraces the position 
of Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī.

15
00:01:01,018 --> 00:01:04,517
And once experiencing that, then
He wants to share that with everyone.

16
00:01:05,564 --> 00:01:08,751
So it’s saying, rādhāra mahimā—
He descended

17
00:01:08,751 --> 00:01:12,958
to broadcast the glories 
of Rādhārāṇī in the world.

18
00:01:12,958 --> 00:01:18,305
And prema-rasa-sīmā—
the limits of Kṛṣṇa-prema.

19
00:01:18,813 --> 00:01:21,180
That’s why Mahāprabhu 
has descended.

20
00:01:26,395 --> 00:01:31,656
sva-bhaktebhyaḥ śuddhāḿ nija-bhajana-mudrām upadiśan 
[Cc: Ādi-līlā, 3.66]

21
00:01:31,856 --> 00:01:34,859
Rūpa Goswāmī says in the 
“Chaitanyāṣṭakam”,

22
00:01:35,587 --> 00:01:39,217
sadopāsyaḥ śrīmān dhṛta-manuja-kāyaiḥ praṇayitāṁ

23
00:01:39,217 --> 00:01:43,257
vahadbhir gīr-vāṇair giriśa-parameṣṭhi-prabhṛtibhiḥ
[Cc: Ādi-līlā, 3.66]

24
00:01:43,257 --> 00:01:50,857
This is so extraordinary [that]
Brahmā and Śiva are disguised 
as human beings,

25
00:01:51,457 --> 00:01:54,829
as are other gods and goddesses,
to come and have a glimpse

26
00:01:55,399 --> 00:02:01,419
of how beautiful Kṛṣṇa looks 
when He is under the influence 
of the heart and halo of Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī—

27
00:02:01,650 --> 00:02:05,198
when Kṛṣṇa’s been converted 
into a devotee.

28
00:02:07,794 --> 00:02:14,733
As Guru Mahārāj identifies 
the concept of Gaura Gadādhar

29
00:02:15,017 --> 00:02:19,781
as the āchārya-līlā 
of Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa.

30
00:02:20,458 --> 00:02:22,637
But still the point is there

31
00:02:22,876 --> 00:02:25,956
that Kṛṣṇa, as He’s become a devotee

32
00:02:28,043 --> 00:02:30,489
and celebrating devotion,

33
00:02:31,089 --> 00:02:35,420
so Her servitors, 
they always want to promote Her.

34
00:02:37,028 --> 00:02:43,659
She, being of a particular nature, 
is always trying to promote Her servitors

35
00:02:46,009 --> 00:02:49,960
to bring them in closer 
connection with Kṛṣṇa.

36
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:53,298
But they know, as the name indicated 
by Śrīla Saraswatī Ṭhākur,

37
00:02:53,298 --> 00:02:59,066
Śrī Vārṣhabhānavi Devī Dayita,

38
00:02:59,066 --> 00:03:04,114
[one] who’s so dear to Vārṣhabhānavi Devī, 
means Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī.

39
00:03:05,821 --> 00:03:09,633
They’re always, they’re 
exclusively promoting Her.

40
00:03:10,971 --> 00:03:16,687
And not out of some just sense
of obligation or loyalty,

41
00:03:16,687 --> 00:03:20,661
you could say, underneath it all
there is a strategy too,

42
00:03:20,661 --> 00:03:25,115
identified by Śrīla Guru Mahārāj as

43
00:03:25,115 --> 00:03:31,039
the incomparable quality 
of Kṛṣṇa conception

44
00:03:31,039 --> 00:03:33,459
and connection that comes 
through Her,

45
00:03:33,459 --> 00:03:37,289
it’s incomparable.

46
00:03:37,289 --> 00:03:41,459
Mahābhāva-svarūpiṇī Rādhā Ṭhākurāṇī.

